## EXAMPLE FINDING

```yaml
finding:
  id: PERF-001
  category: Performance
  subcategory: Render
  severity: MEDIUM
  file: src/pages/general-foreman/GeneralForemanEquipmentLogs.tsx
  line: 200-250
  observed_condition: |
    Component re-renders on every parent state change because
    filter function is recreated on each render.
  evidence: |
    const filterLogs = (logs) => {
      return logs.filter(log => log.status === selectedStatus);
    };
    // Called inline, new reference each render
    {filterLogs(logs).map(...)}
  impact: |
    With 500 log entries, filtering runs unnecessarily on unrelated
    state changes. Estimated 50-100ms wasted per interaction.
  recommendation: |
    Wrap filterLogs in useMemo with [logs, selectedStatus] deps.
  dod: |
    1. React DevTools shows no re-render on unrelated state change
    2. Filtering only runs when logs or selectedStatus changes
    3. No functional regression
  effort: XS
  dependencies: none
```

